reviewText: I​ had a lot of lagging issues with this project.
T​echnical errors from the programing tool don't allow me to code the exercises, awful experience and a waste of time.
Unfortunately, I thought it should be less technical than what I saw in the introduction!I need to cancel my enrollment  and my subscription too!
Don't waste your money on this course-
Poor one. Expected better
This Guided project was too short

The content of this workshop  strikes a perfect balance of theory and practice for such a short course.  In that, its perfect, five stars.I am not a fan of markdown pages, which it uses extensively.  Its a matter of taste though.I would have liked slides and R code to download.  But the markdown pages do both, I suppose.The last side, which gives information on future studies,  is invaluable to thoe who want to continue.I would certainly want to do this again for a topic I care about.
the interface is not good- hard to use
I have no any idea before I took this course. Some of the contents are not clear for me. I need more explanation for some concepts and practical application.
Having completed it, I'm not sure I understand what the point of it was.

Interesting topic, but poorly constructed course. Materials laid out without much structure. Practice quiz and final quiz have discrepancy in answers. Overall, not clear how the project fit in the big picture.
there was no subtitles which wasted a lot of my time as it was little difficult to understand the teachers english in a few places.
Not to bad for being a short guided course. Concise and a good overview. After this you may very well do a serious course if you want to get anywhere

Good overall. Theory was not well-explained at the end of the video (around chapter 15). Some confusion about when to use stationarity transformation with the real-world example as some tests (Box-Ljung) were not explained in the introductory session.
Need more in-depth course material.
this is simple and great. but no subtitle. so it's hard to me to undestand the english. and rhyme is not well performed
